  "text": "Only good-quality tracks identified as pions or kaons [CITATION_1] and inconsistent with originating from any primary vertex are used. Tracks used to reconstruct an η or φ candidate are each required to be consistent with coming from a common secondary vertex and to have p T > 0.4 GeV/c. The π + π − invariant mass in the η decay must be larger than 0.52 GeV/c 2 to reject K",
